title: Taiwan CPI Transportation
description: The transportation sub-index of the CPI basket in Taiwan increased to 107.90 points in October of 2022 from 107.78 points in September of 2022. CPI Transportation in Taiwan averaged 97.58 points from 1981 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 113.13 points in July of 2008 and a record low of 83.72 points in June of 1988. This page provides - Taiwan Cpi Transportation- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Directorate-General of Budget, Accounting and Statistics, Taiwan
